subSubSection.paragraph:
Paratrilobus tankhoyensis
sp. nov. is most similar to
P. expugnator (Tsalolichin, 1976)
in body size (Tsalolichin 1976). The new species differs from it in the comparatively thin body ( a = 57–71 vs a = 32–44 in
P. expugnator
), shorter and thicker tail ( c = 23–38, cʹ = 2.3–3.7 vs c = 8.2–10.4, cʹ = 5.0– 7.5 in
P. expugnator
), shorter stoma (stoma length 45–55 µm vs 70–80 µm long in
P. expugnator
), and shorter spicules (spicules length 70–76 µm vs 90 µm long in
P. expugnator
) (Tsalolichin 1976).
